3
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:58,016
Have you had enough yet?

4
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,981
[Groans]

5
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:08,986
Are you ready now?

6
00:01:57,993 --> 00:02:00,996
[Birds Chirping]

7
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:21,016
[Birds Chirping]

8
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:59,012
[Audience Applauding]

9
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:03,016
Thank you.

10
00:03:04,017 --> 00:03:07,980
And every single
free choice you make...

11
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:12,985
arises from either a thought of love
or a thought of fear.

12
00:03:12,985 --> 00:03:15,988
- There is no other choice.
- [Shutter Clicks]

13
00:03:15,988 --> 00:03:18,991
And if I had one thing to say
about what we're trying...

14
00:03:18,991 --> 00:03:21,994
to understand here tonight,
it would be– it would be this:

15
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:26,999
That feeling inside of you...

16
00:03:26,999 --> 00:03:31,003
that love inside of you-

17
00:03:31,003 --> 00:03:33,005
that's God...

18
00:03:33,005 --> 00:03:37,009
eXpressing through you as you.

19
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:41,013
Yes?

20
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:43,015
- [Microphone Feedback]
- My name is Daisy...

21
00:03:43,015 --> 00:03:45,017
- and I just wanted to say I loved your book.
- Thank you, Daisy.

22
00:03:46,018 --> 00:03:50,981
And I'm-I'm feeling like I finally understand
what it means to be awake in my own life.

23
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,983
- Feels good, doesn't it?
- It's totally amazing!

24
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:55,986
- Mm-hmm.
- I walk around feeling like I've been given a secret.

25
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:57,988
Well...

26
00:03:57,988 --> 00:04:01,992
- the secret is out!
- [Laughing]

27
00:04:01,992 --> 00:04:03,994
- [Applause]
- The problem I've been having...

28
00:04:03,994 --> 00:04:06,997
is that some of my friends,
even my family–

29
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:12,002
If I say anything remotely spiritual,
they get this glazed look on their face.

30
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:14,004
- [Man] Ah.
- And I know that look...

31
00:04:14,004 --> 00:04:18,008
because it's the same look I've had,
or used to have, every day of my life.

32
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:22,012
I know eXactly what that feels like.

33
00:04:22,012 --> 00:04:26,016
And the good news is,
you're not crazy.

34
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:28,018
- Good. [Laughs]
- 'Cause we're both crazy.

35
00:04:28,018 --> 00:04:30,020
- [Laughing]
- And if that's the case...

36
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:33,982
- we're in very good company.
- [Laughing, Applauding]

37
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:41,990
Instead of worrying about
what people think about you...

38
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:46,995
concentrate on
what you think about you.

39
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:48,997
- [Applause]
- That's important.

40
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,005
Any regrets?

41
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:01,009
- Many.
- Care to name a few?

42
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:04,012
- You're not a lawyer, are you?
- [Audience Laughing]

43
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:12,020
I wish that I could have come to
this point in my life without hurting-

44
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:23,991
wish I'd come to this point
in my life without...

45
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:25,993
hurting so many people–

46
00:05:27,995 --> 00:05:30,998
especially the people I've loved.

47
00:05:31,999 --> 00:05:34,001
But without them...

48
00:05:34,001 --> 00:05:38,005
I might not have come
to this point in my life.

49
00:05:38,005 --> 00:05:40,007
See, it's important
for all of us to remember...

50
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:43,010
that the universe
is conspiring in our favor-

51
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:46,013
always, and in all ways...

52
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:49,016
despite circumstances
and appearances...

53
00:05:49,016 --> 00:05:53,020
or most importantly,
our perception of them.

54
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,981
- You've got a lot of nerve!
- I'm sorry?

55
00:05:55,981 --> 00:05:58,984
- You're a hypocrite.
- It's all right. It's all right. It's all right.

56
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:00,986
Standing up there preaching
about God and love.

57
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:03,989
You've been married
and divorced a lot.

58
00:06:03,989 --> 00:06:06,992
If you talk to God, how come you can't
keep a commitment with a woman?

59
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:28,013
[Man] I can't tell you how many times
I've asked myself that same question.

60
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:32,017
The women in my life...

61
00:06:33,018 --> 00:06:35,020
are all wonderful.

62
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:40,984
They treated me a whole lot
better than I treated them.

63
00:06:40,984 --> 00:06:42,986
I betrayed them.

64
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:45,989
I let them down.
I let my kids down too.

65
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:47,991
I admit that.

66
00:06:47,991 --> 00:06:51,995
More than that I cannot say
without invading their privacy...

67
00:06:51,995 --> 00:06:53,997
and that I am not gonna do.

68
00:06:55,999 --> 00:07:02,005
What I can do is love
as much as I can from where I am.

69
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:06,009
To make every gesture and action
sponsored by love.

70
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:10,013
- Sounds to me like you've written a book of lies.
- [Audience Murmuring]

71
00:07:11,014 --> 00:07:16,019
If what you're asking me is, did I make
all of this stuff up, the answer is no.

72
00:07:16,019 --> 00:07:19,982
I've wondered what you're wondering.

73
00:07:19,982 --> 00:07:22,985
??will anyone believe me,
believe what I'm saying...

74
00:07:22,985 --> 00:07:24,987
believe where this came from?"

75
00:07:25,988 --> 00:07:27,990
And I guess that
that's up to you–

76
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,993
to each of you.

77
00:07:30,993 --> 00:07:33,996
I only hope that you don't
disqualify or marginalize the message...

78
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:38,000
because it's coming through
such a fallible messenger.

79
00:07:46,008 --> 00:07:49,011
My name is Kay,
and I just wanted to thank you...

80
00:07:49,011 --> 00:07:52,014
for admitting your mistakes.

81
00:07:56,018 --> 00:07:58,020
[Man] Well, thank you, Kay-
um, and all of you.

82
00:07:58,020 --> 00:08:01,982
But the truth of it is, I'm still making
those mistakes to this day.

83
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:07,988
That's why these conversations with God
are such a miracle for me.

84
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:09,990
They-They came out of a need–

85
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:12,993
a desperate personal need–
for me to change my life.

86
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:16,997
And, um, you know, uh...

87
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:21,001
if I've been successful
at it in the way I'd like–

88
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:23,003
I don't know,
but-but it's the way it happened...

89
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:27,007
and it's the way it's–
it's still happening.

90
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:29,009
[Kay]
My question is...

91
00:08:29,009 --> 00:08:32,012
if God has one message–

92
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:35,015
his most important
message to all of us–

93
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:40,020
and you could put it in one paragraph,
what would it be?

94
00:08:44,983 --> 00:08:47,986
[Man] Well, I could fit it
into five words.

95
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:51,990
??You've got me all wrong."

96
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,993
- [Cheering]
- Thank you.

97
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:57,996
Thank you.
Thank you.

98
00:08:57,996 --> 00:09:00,999
Thank you.
Thank you.

99
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,002
Good night.

100
00:09:05,003 --> 00:09:07,005
[Crowd Chanting]
Neale! Neale! Neale!

101
00:09:07,005 --> 00:09:13,011
Neale! Neale! Neale!
Neale! Neale! Neale!

102
00:09:15,013 --> 00:09:17,015
[Rain Falling]

103
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:26,984
[Woman]
Here's your plane ticket. You're on the 10:00.

104
00:09:26,984 --> 00:09:29,987
Thanks for everything,
and I'll see you in New York.

105
00:09:48,005 --> 00:09:51,008
[Thunder Rumbling]

106
00:10:40,015 --> 00:10:43,018
[Vehicle Approaching]

107
00:10:43,018 --> 00:10:45,020
[Tires Screeching]

108
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:51,985
[Siren wailing]

109
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:05,999
- Still nothing, huh?
- I'm trying, honey.

110
00:11:05,999 --> 00:11:09,002
You could have fooled me. Look,
I don't get this. I've got eXperience–

111
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:14,007
Your eXperience has nothing to do with anything.
And we've been over this, Neale.

112
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,009
- [Groans]
- As long as that bow tie's around your neck...

113
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:19,012
nobody's going to take
a chance on hiring you.

114
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:23,016
Really?
So, what is it eXactly...

115
00:11:23,016 --> 00:11:26,019
that you people do around here?

116
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:30,983
Mostly we hand out checks to people
who blame us for their problems.

117
00:11:32,985 --> 00:11:34,987
Sorry.

118
00:11:34,987 --> 00:11:36,989
What did the hospital say?

119
00:11:36,989 --> 00:11:39,992
Well, they said I should start
feeling better in a few days...

120
00:11:39,992 --> 00:11:42,995
but, uh, it's been
almost a month now.

121
00:11:42,995 --> 00:11:45,998
Wow. They seem
to have missed something.

122
00:11:45,998 --> 00:11:49,001
- What?
- Neale...

123
00:11:49,001 --> 00:11:51,003
you have a broken neck.

124
00:11:58,010 --> 00:12:00,012
[Lighter Flicks]

125
00:12:04,016 --> 00:12:08,020
- [Knocking]
- [Man] Mr. Walsch, it's Michael.

126
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:10,981
[Knocking]

127
00:12:10,981 --> 00:12:13,984
Come on, Mr. Walsch.
I know you're in there.

128
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:16,987
[Neale]
No, I'm not.

129
00:12:19,990 --> 00:12:21,992
- You're three months behind on your rent.
- [Door Closes]

130
00:12:22,993 --> 00:12:24,995
I told you. I lost my–

131
00:12:24,995 --> 00:12:27,998
- Your job.
- Job, yeah.

132
00:12:27,998 --> 00:12:30,000
Yes, I know. And I'm sorry
about your accident, Neale.

133
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:34,004
But I'm not gonna lose my job
because you lost yours.

134
00:12:35,005 --> 00:12:37,007
Come on. I'm out there.

135
00:12:37,007 --> 00:12:39,009
Every day, I am.
I'm trying.

136
00:12:44,014 --> 00:12:46,016
Isn't there someone you can call?

137
00:12:48,018 --> 00:12:50,979
No. Those calls were made
a long time ago.

138
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:52,981
I mean, I got–

139
00:12:54,983 --> 00:12:57,986
I got nowhere to go.

140
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,993
5:00, Neale.

141
00:13:31,019 --> 00:13:35,983
[No Audible Dialogue]

142
00:13:47,995 --> 00:13:50,998
[No Audible Dialogue]

143
00:14:31,997 --> 00:14:33,999
- [Thunder Rumbling]
- [Blows]

144
00:14:37,002 --> 00:14:39,004
[Inhales, Groans]

145
00:14:42,007 --> 00:14:44,009
[Children Chattering,
Laughing]

146
00:14:44,009 --> 00:14:46,011
[Child Babbling]

147
00:14:46,011 --> 00:14:48,013
[Woman]
Okay, who's ready for bed?

148
00:14:48,013 --> 00:14:51,016
I'm coming in there.
I hope you got your R.J. 's on.

149
00:14:51,016 --> 00:14:55,020
