222
00:22:05,993 --> 00:22:09,997
Just a minute.
[Groans]

223
00:22:09,997 --> 00:22:14,001
- Morning.
- Uh, good morning.

224
00:22:14,001 --> 00:22:18,005
Name is Oscar. How about you
step out of that tent for a minute?

225
00:22:18,005 --> 00:22:20,007
Uh, what for?

226
00:22:22,009 --> 00:22:26,013
I know you got in late,
but I run things around here...

227
00:22:26,013 --> 00:22:29,016
- and you should be aware of the rules.
- Uh, rules?

228
00:22:29,016 --> 00:22:31,018
Yeah.
I'll walk you through them.

229
00:22:31,018 --> 00:22:34,980
How about you come a little bit
closer so I don't have to yell?

230
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:37,983
- Okay.
- Okay.

231
00:22:37,983 --> 00:22:40,986
Rent is $25 per week.

232
00:22:40,986 --> 00:22:43,989
Over there
you've got your bathrooms.

233
00:22:43,989 --> 00:22:46,992
Now, our maid quit
about a month ago...

234
00:22:46,992 --> 00:22:49,995
so we'd appreciate it
if you would clean up after yourself.

235
00:22:49,995 --> 00:22:51,997
- Okay.
- Those cabins back there–

236
00:22:52,998 --> 00:22:56,001
- freight on them: 75 per week.
- Right.

237
00:22:56,001 --> 00:23:00,005
Now, down by the water
you've got another picnic area.

238
00:23:00,005 --> 00:23:02,007
Those are reserved for real campers
and real campers only.

239
00:23:03,008 --> 00:23:04,009
Uh, real campers?

240
00:23:04,009 --> 00:23:07,012
They usually arrive by automobile.

